@CDCgov Remember when you combined the COVID &amp; flu numbers on your website - listed everything that involved COVID together but not separate (to inflate the COVID numbers)
THEN said the flu was abnormally low the following year (also to inflate COVID numbers)?

...it was blatant 😆 https://t.co/6rK9uhd4kU

@CDCgov Until 3 years ago, only in the United States, 6,000 people died each year from flu. People affected before and now had weak immune systems. 
It is not the flu or the nickname they want to give it. 
All depends on the person.

@CDCgov Done.
Got it in October. 
Also got bivalent covid booster 2 weeks ago.

@CDCgov My mom got a flu shot every year,  for at least 30-35 years before she passed away. 
And every year,  she became very ill. 
So excuse me if I pass on that 💉💉 too.
